.TH HSH 1 "5 May 2022" "0.01" "simple_shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple Shell for ALX School
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
[command] [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
(Simple Shell) is an end of semester project for Students at Holberton School where we understand, explore and build a working functional simple shell program.

The shell is a command that read lines from either a file or the terminal, interprets them, and generally executes other commands. It is the program that is running when a suer logs into the system. 


.B Overview

The simple shell is a simplified iteration of a command line interpreter similar to
.B bash or
.B dash.
.I FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.SH OPTIONS
.B Simple Shell
operates in both
.I interactive
and 
.I non-interactive
mode. The user may initiate
.B simple shell
and begin working or initate
.B simple shell
using commands meant to be run by the program.
.SH ARGUMENTS
The first argument, argument 0 is understood to be the command to be run by
.B simple shell
and arguments following as modifier or options.
.SH Return value
The return value of a simple command is its exit status
.SH Example
.PP

$./hsh

$

$ls 

